      { title: "Quantitative Skills in Extracts", body: "Index numbers, % changes, real vs nominal, trade balance, Gini coefficient, concentration ratios. Always show your working — method marks available even if the final answer is wrong." },
      { title: "25-Mark Essay Structure", body: "KAA₁ (Knowledge, Application, Analysis: Point → Explain → Diagram → Apply) → Evaluation₁ → KAA₂ → Evaluation₂ → Overall Judgement. Aim for 50/50 KAA vs eval." },
      { title: "Paper 3 Data Response", body: "Two extracts: one micro, one macro. 12-mark data questions then 25-mark essay. Always use figures from the extract — examiners reward contextual application." }
