      { q: "A country runs a current account (CA) deficit. This most likely means:", opts: ["The government is spending more than it receives in tax", "Imports of goods, services and income exceed exports", "Inflation exceeds the target rate", "The budget is in surplus"], correct: 1, exp: "CA deficit = outflow of payments (imports, income, transfers) exceeds inflows. Distinct from the fiscal/budget deficit." },
      { q: "Strongest evaluation for a 25-mark essay on fiscal policy?", opts: ["It might not work", "Time lags and crowding out reduce the multiplier, especially in an open economy with high MPM", "The government can always spend more", "Monetary policy is better"], correct: 1, exp: "Strong evaluation names the mechanism, links to context. Vague evaluation scores Level 1." }
